    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="468"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.22793/6–2746</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-18">July 18,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The receipt is acknowledged of
                    your letter of June 27, 1946,<note n="17" xml:id="d468fn17">Not printed.</note>
                    regarding the necessity of providing the War Department with funds to continue
                    the Chinese Air Force Training Program after June 30, 1946.</p>
                <pb facs="0791" n="781" xml:id="pg_781"/>
                <p>Reference is made in this connection to my letter of July 10, 1946,<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d468fn18">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_751">p. 751</ref>.</note> in
                    which it was stated that on June 29, 1946, a check for $4,000,000 was delivered
                    by representatives of the Chinese Government to the War Department as an initial
                    payment in support of the Air Force Training Program after June 30, 1946. The
                    Department of State will continue to make every effort to obtain from the
                    Chinese Government the balance due so that there will be no interruption in the
                    program.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dean Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
